#. Tag: title
#: adm_sudo.xml:510
#, no-c-format
msgid "Common Use Cases"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: adm_sudo.xml:512
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Although the default configuration is often sufficient for simple setups and "
"desktop environments, custom configurations can be very useful."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: adm_sudo.xml:518
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using &sudo; without &rootuser; Password"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: adm_sudo.xml:519
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In cases with special restrictions ( <quote>user X can only run command Y as "
"&rootuser;</quote> ) it is not possible. In other cases, it is still "
"favorable to have some kind of separation. By convention, members of the "
"group <systemitem class=\"groupname\">wheel</systemitem> can run all "
"commands with &sudo; as root."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: adm_sudo.xml:528
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Add yourself to the <systemitem class=\"groupname\">wheel</systemitem> group"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: adm_sudo.xml:532
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If your user account is not already member of the <systemitem class="
"\"groupname\">wheel</systemitem> group, add it by running <command>sudo "
"usermod -a -G wheel <replaceable>USERNAME</replaceable></command> and "
"logging out and in again. Verify that the change was successful by running "
"<command>groups <replaceable>USERNAME</replaceable></command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: adm_sudo.xml:542
#, no-c-format
msgid "Make authentication with the invoking user's password the default."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: adm_sudo.xml:545
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Create the file <filename>/etc/sudoers.d/userpw</filename> with "
"<command>visudo</command> (see <xref linkend=\"sec.sudo.conf.edit\"/> ) and "
"add:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: adm_sudo.xml:550
#, no-c-format
msgid "Defaults !targetpw"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: adm_sudo.xml:553
#, no-c-format
msgid "Select a new default rule."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: adm_sudo.xml:556
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Depending on whether you want users to re-enter their passwords, uncomment "
"the specific line in <filename>/etc/sudoers</filename> and comment out the "
"default rule."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: adm_sudo.xml:561
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"## Uncomment to allow members of group wheel to execute any command\n"
"# %wheel ALL=(ALL) ALL\n"
"\n"
"## Same thing without a password\n"
"# %wheel ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD: ALL\n"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: adm_sudo.xml:570
#, no-c-format
msgid "Make the default rule more restrictive"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: adm_sudo.xml:573
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Comment out or remove the allow-everything rule in <filename>/etc/sudoers</"
"filename> :"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: adm_sudo.xml:577
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"ALL     ALL=(ALL) ALL   # WARNING! Only use this together with 'Defaults "
"targetpw'!"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: adm_sudo.xml:579
#, no-c-format
msgid "Dangerous rule in sudoers"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: adm_sudo.xml:580
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Do not forget this step, otherwise <emphasis>any</emphasis> user can execute "
"<emphasis>any</emphasis> command as &rootuser;!"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: adm_sudo.xml:587
#, no-c-format
msgid "Test the configuration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: adm_sudo.xml:590
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Try to run &sudo; as member and non-member of <systemitem class=\"groupname"
"\">wheel</systemitem> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: adm_sudo.xml:594
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"<prompt>&exampleuser_plain;:~ &gt; </prompt>groups\n"
"users wheel\n"
"<prompt>&exampleuser_plain;:~ &gt; </prompt>sudo id -un\n"
"&exampleuser_plain;'s password:\n"
"root\n"
"<prompt>&exampleuserII_plain;:~ &gt; </prompt>groups\n"
"users\n"
"<prompt>&exampleuserII_plain;:~ &gt; </prompt>sudo id -un\n"
"&exampleuserII_plain; is not in the sudoers file.  This incident will be "
"reported.\n"
"          "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: adm_sudo.xml:610
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using &sudo; with &xvendor; Applications"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: adm_sudo.xml:611
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When starting graphical applications with &sudo;, you will encounter the "
"following error:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: adm_sudo.xml:615
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"&prompt.sudo;xterm\n"
"xterm: Xt error: Can't open display: %s\n"
"xterm: DISPLAY is not set\n"
"      "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: adm_sudo.xml:620
#, no-c-format
msgid "&yast; will pick the ncurses interface instead of the graphical one."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: adm_sudo.xml:623
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To use &xvendor; in applications started with &sudo;, the environment "
"variables <envar>DISPLAY</envar> and <envar>XAUTHORITY</envar> need to be "
"propagated. To configure this, create the file <filename>/etc/sudoers.d/"
"xorg</filename> , (see <xref linkend=\"sec.sudo.conf.edit\"/> ) and add the "
"following line:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: adm_sudo.xml:630
#, no-c-format
msgid "Defaults env_keep += \"DISPLAY XAUTHORITY\""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: adm_sudo.xml:631
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If not set already, set the <envar>XAUTHORITY</envar> variable as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: adm_sudo.xml:634
#, no-c-format
msgid "export XAUTHORITY=~/.Xauthority"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: adm_sudo.xml:635
#, no-c-format
msgid "Now &xvendor; applications can be run as usual:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: adm_sudo.xml:638
#, no-c-format
msgid "sudo yast2"
msgstr ""

